text: West Muna Regency () is a new regency of Southeast Sulawesi, Indonesia, established in 2014 under Act No.14 of 2014, dated 23 July 2014 by separation from the Muna Regency. It covers an area of 1,022.9 km2, and the districts comprising it had a population of 71,632 at the 2010 Census;Biro Pusat Statistik, Jakarta, 2011. the latest official estimate (as at 2018) is 78,630.Badan Pusat Statistik, Jakarta, 2019. The administrative centre lies at Laworo. ==Administrative districts== The West Muna Regency, created in 2014, is divided into the following eleven districts (kecamatan), tabulated below with their 2010 Census populations.Biro Pusat Statistik, Jakarta, 2011. {| class="sortable wikitable" |- !
